# Renderer3DSystem

## Purpose
Draws all 3D models into an offscreen render target each frame, before the 2D pass (ADR 0007). Reads
the engine config for the 3D shader + render-target UUIDs and resolves both — plus each model — from
the resource map. Returns early (no-op) when the engine config, resource map, perspective camera, or
the configured render target / shader are absent.

On the first valid frame it allocates a dynamic GPU vertex/index buffer pair and resolves the model
shader into Renderer3DDataSingletonComponent (deferred), then returns; drawing begins the next frame.
On later frames it binds the render target (clearing its colour + depth and enabling depth testing),
binds the shader and buffers, and for every entity with a ModelComponent + WorldTransformComponent
uploads the model's geometry and the combined view-projection × world matrix, then issues an indexed
draw. The render target's colour buffer is registered in the texture map (by ResourceManagerSystem)
under the same UUID, so the 2D pass samples the result as an ordinary texture.

The pass runs strictly before Renderer2DSystem: that system declares a read of
Renderer3DDataSingletonComponent purely to order the two passes, so the 2D pass samples the current
frame's 3D image and the window back buffer is rebound last.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read | 3D shader + render-target UUIDs |
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read | Model map, render-target map, shader map |
| PerspectiveCameraComponent | read | 3D view-projection; system no-ops if absent |
| ModelComponent | read | References a loaded model by UUID |
| WorldTransformComponent | read | World placement of each model |
| Renderer3DDataSingletonComponent | write | GPU buffers + resolved shader |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Renderer3DDataSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Holds the GPU vertex/index buffers and the resolved model shader; created on the first valid frame |
